    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The GNPS network from the 51 spectra was rebuilt, with selected parameter values to obtain the more consistent network with the one reported by the authors (see Supplementary File 1, Note S2). This network contains two large connected components of respective size 21 and 11, two pairs, and 15 spectra remaining isolated. The main components to be explained (disjoint cliques of size above 3, as well as pairs with similarity above 0.9) were extracted (findGNPSComponents method), leading to 5 disjoint cliques, in addition to the initial 4 connected components of the network.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper does report component counts (2 large connected components, 2 pairs, 15 isolated spectra; 5 disjoint cliques extracted), but the title claims to 'reproduce the count' while the research_question and expected_outputs focus on pattern P70 and component 8 metrics\u2014a mismatch. The title is narrower in scope than the actual research question.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-025-01051-y",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
