    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The title ('Reproduce the count of GNPS components') is narrower and different in focus from the research_question (which asks about pattern P70 F1-score on component 8). This is a significant scope mismatch.",
        "The research_question references specific component and pattern identifiers ('component 8', 'pattern P70', precursor m/z values 370.1283 and 404.0891) that do not appear in the paper passages. These appear to be either fabricated or from supplementary materials not provided.",
        "The expected_outputs claim specific F1-score values (1.0 for P70, 0.9 minimum recall for all top-5) that are not supported by the paper's reported aggregate statistics (mean F1-score 0.89, minimum 0.55, minimum recall 0.9).",
        "The card conflates two different tasks: (1) reproducing component counts (title), and (2) validating pattern metrics for a specific component (research_question and expected_outputs). These should be separate cards."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 4,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:51:58.634062+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragmentation-pattern-extraction-and-ranking/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We propose an innovative de novo strategy for searching for exact fragmentation patterns within collections of MS/MS spectra. This approach is based on (i) a new representation of spectra as graphs of m/z differences, and (ii) an efficient frequent-subgraph mining algorithm... maximal subgraphs (i.e. closed subgraphs) are mined at the selected frequency threshold... select the patterns that best explain these components... patterns explaining each component were found, with a minimum recall of 0.9 and a mean F1-score of 0.89",
      "asbval:note": "All core claims verified: closed subgraph mining of m/z differences, ranking by recall/precision/F1-score metrics, and network component explanation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-025-01051-y",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragmentation-pattern-extraction-and-ranking",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Extract frequent fragmentation patterns from collections of MS/MS spectra by mining closed subgraphs of m/z differences, then rank patterns by their ability to explain network components using recall, precision, and size metrics.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:53:02.518643+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragmentation-pattern-extraction-and-ranking/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Importantly, such approaches do not require any information from spectral or molecular databases, nor any knowledge about molecular formulas... This new graph representation is exact and makes no assumption about the fragmentation path leading to a given fragment ion, nor about the molecular formula of the precursor.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly states no database or molecular formula requirement.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-025-01051-y",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragmentation-pattern-extraction-and-ranking",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "discovery of shared fragmentation signatures independent of spectral database thresholds and molecular formula knowledge",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:53:02.518643+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragmentation-pattern-extraction-and-ranking/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The spectra are converted to Directed Acyclic Graphs built on a common set of edge labels extracted from the whole spectra collection... The search for common patterns of m/z differences (edges) among the fragmentation graphs is performed by an efficient Frequent Subgraph Mining (FSM) algorithm... spectra common to at least two spectra",
      "asbval:note": "Minimum frequency threshold of 2 is standard in the paper's examples.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-025-01051-y",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragmentation-pattern-extraction-and-ranking",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when you have a collection of MS/MS spectra (\u22652 spectra) and wish to identify fragmentation signatures common to subsets of those spectra.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:53:02.518643+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragmentation-pattern-extraction-and-ranking/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The coupling of mineMS2 to molecular networks [27] is a valuable strategy to focus on the patterns that best-explain each component of the network... The package thus enables to (1) automatically extracts connected components, cliques of a selected minimum size, and pairs of spectra of a specified minimum similarity, and (2) select the patterns that best explain these components.",
      "asbval:note": "Explicit integration with GNPS networks for component and clique explanation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-025-01051-y",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragmentation-pattern-extraction-and-ranking",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Particularly valuable when coupled to GNPS molecular networks to explain why spectral pairs or cliques cluster together",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:53:02.518643+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragmentation-pattern-extraction-and-ranking/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Direct matching to databases, however, is limited by the amount of available MS/MS data obtained from pure standards... Importantly, such approaches do not require any information from spectral or molecular databases, nor any knowledge about molecular formulas.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper emphasizes de novo approach independent of databases and formulas.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-025-01051-y",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragmentation-pattern-extraction-and-ranking",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "when seeking patterns that distinguish one set of spectra from others without requiring precursor molecular formulas or external spectral libraries",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:53:02.518643+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
